war Italian neo-realist filmmaking; whereas Jude and The claim are approached as both literary adaptations (a continuing strand in British cinema history) and examples of other reworked genres (the road movie, the western).This lively study of his work, written in a wholly accessible style, will engage all those who have followed his career as well as those with a wide-ranging interest in British cinema.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aMotion picture producers and directorszGreat BritainvBiography. 4aFilm and Media Studies 2019. 7aPERFORMING ARTS / Film & Video / History & Criticism.2bisacsh  a24 Hour Party People.  aHollywood genres.  aIn This World.  aMichael Winterbottom.  aThames TV documentaries.  aThe Road to Guantánamo.  aWelcome to Sarajevo.  aWonderland.  aerotic drama.  arealism.  arealist sex.  ascience-fiction thriller.  atelevision career.1 aMcFarlane, Brian, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWilliams, Deane, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aWilliams, Deane, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertManchester University Press 1986 - 2013 eBook Packagez978311128363040uhttps://doi.org/10.7765/978152614168240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781526141682423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781526141682/original  a978-3-11-128363-0  Manchester University Press 1986 - 2013 eBook Packagec1986d2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles